some philly good eats‚Äî

@pizzeriavetri really good classic neapolitan style pizza. there‚Äôs traditional flavors like margherita and pepperoni, but also some really unique flavors like the seasonal roasted lamb pizza. trust me, and order the spinach pizza here- onions, roasted garlic, mozzarella, ricotta fonduta, parmesan, and chili flakes on light yet chewy dough *chef‚Äôs kiss*

@cheufishtown_nunu asian fusion ramen bar with a menu of asian inspired noodle bowls, soups, and small plates, sushi, and japanese-style pub food. great food and atmosphere. the scallion rangoons appetizer here is a must order!

@doubleknot_phl one of my all time favorite restaurants in philly that i find myself always wanting to go back to. really tasty sushi, pan-asian cuisine, and robotayaki enjoyed in an intimate underground izakaya atmosphere. a great spot for any occasion.

@charlie_was vegan restaurant serving creative plant-based small plates and excellent cocktails. my favorites were their espresso martini, ricotta, and silken tofu & mushroom ramen.

@grancaffelaquila i haven‚Äôt gotten the chance to have a full dining experience here yet (although i‚Äôve heard great things!), but i go just for their gelato, and it is phenomenal. my go-to flavor combo is pistachio + fondente, but i like to mix it up too, and you really can‚Äôt go wrong with any of the flavors here.

