time for another philly food round up‚Ä¶

@surayaphilly an all day specialty market, garden, and restaurant that will definitely not disappoint. the beautiful atmosphere with incredibly flavorful and tasty lebanese food and cocktails is perfect for a special occasion meal. for the full experience, i definitely recommend doing ‚Äúa taste of suraya‚Äù at dinner which will let you try a full spread of dips and a lot of variety.

@dottiesdonuts perfectly chewy, yeasty, and not too sweet vegan donuts that were worth going out of the way for! flavors here are unique and creative, and they are constantly changing, so i will definitely be back.

@kfar_cafe an israeli bakery and cafe right rittenhouse square. all the food was delicious, but the pastries were the star of the show. get the pistachio sticky bun or chocolate babka. trust me. highly recommend as a relaxed breakfast/brunch spot.

@branzinophilly an italian byob restaurant with tasty house-made pastas and food and an elegant outdoor seating area which is perfect for these warmer months coming up.

@weckerlys may be my favorite ice cream shop in philly! they focus on using local ingredients to create high quality small batch ice cream and ice cream sandwiches. they have both classic and changing specialty flavors, and every flavor i‚Äôve tried here has been delicious.

